# Glitch NinjaTrader packaging

## Release artifact

- Treat customer-facing NinjaTrader zips as release artifacts, not workspace snapshots.
- Prefer compiled assembly exports for customer downloads unless the user explicitly wants source distribution.

## Bundled fallback resources

- If static defaults such as `PropFirmRules.json` are required at runtime, prefer a bundled C# fallback before export.
- Do not rely on manual post-export zip mutation for JSON or XML unless the exact import structure has been validated.

## Package hygiene

- Inspect every exported archive before publish.
- Do not ship docs, TSV runtime state, secrets, formulas, provider internals, ports, cryptography details, or other internal material in customer packages.
- Stage inspected release zips under `apps/download` or the chosen release area before pointing a public download link at them.
